What is ARK Survival Evolved Mobile ?

Dive into the ultimate mobile dino-adventure with ARK: Survival Evolved! A massive game world combines with 80+ unique dinosaurs and primal creatures for you to capture and tame - making for a survival experience bar-none. Meet up with other players and friends in this Jurassic-era world, to form tribes and work together to build colonies of survivors. 

Based on the genre-defining adventure from PC and consoles, ARK: Survival Evolved challenges you to survive and thrive on a mysterious island, where you start out alone and unarmed. Gather resources and craft tools to build shelter and hunt. Expand your domain while capturing and taming dinosaurs to do your bidding. Make new friends online, form tribes, and build mighty structures to defend against man and mega-predators alike!

Features of ARK: Survival Evolved include: 

- 80+ Dinosaurs: Use cunning strategy and tactics to tame, train, ride and breed the many dinosaurs and other primeval creatures roaming the dynamic, persistent ecosystems across land, sea, air, and even underground. 
- Discover: Explore a massive living and breathing prehistoric landscape as you find the means to survive, thrive, and escape on the Ark.
- Craft and Build: Using any means necessary to survive, craft weapons, clothes, and items, and build shelters, villages, or even large cities. 
- Survive Alone or With Others: Group up with, or prey on, hundreds of other players in a large-scale online world or choose to go it alone in single-player mode.
- Join a Tribe: The 'Tribe' system encourages cooperation, by supporting dynamic parties to share resources, XP, and re-spawn points.

The game includes an optional Primal Pass subscription available on a monthly or yearly basis. The subscription removes all ads, gives you a 2x XP boost, and provides access to both preferred servers and to preferred slots on free servers. Subscribers receive an insignia next to their name to indicate their status as Primal Pass holders and will receive special news and updates from time to time.. family friendly pg clean

snippet.title: Amber Lawrence Top 10 Songs of all time! - Country Music World
snippet.description:
Mick and Jay have compiled the Country Music World Top 10 Amber Lawrence songs of all time!

Amber Lawrence is an award-winning singer-songwriter whose career keeps going from strength to strength. 
Each year seems to get better and busier for Amber, with 2016 seeing the engaging entertainer win Female Artist of the Year at the Country Music Channel Oz Awards, plus the people’s Choice Award for Female Artist of the Year, at the Tamworth Country Music Festival.  
Amber was also extremely honoured to receive an Australia Day Bronze Achievement Award for her contribution to veterans and their families, via her work with DefenceCare. 
The awards keep rolling in for this hardworking Australian, who’s biggest career achievement to date was being awarded the iconic and prestigious ‘Female Artist of the Year’ award, at the 2015 CMAA Golden Guitar awards. 
This was quickly followed up with the Country Music Channel 2015 ‘Female Oz Artist of the Year’ Award.  
This is the first time in history that a female artist has won both awards in one year. In 2016, Amber has released not one, but two albums – the critically acclaimed 5th studio album “Happy Ever After”, and her high selling children’s album “The Kid’s Gone Country”.  And 2017 is shaping up to be another big one for Amber, with two Golden Guitar nominations – for Female Artist of the Year and for Vocal Collaboration of the year for her hit song “Cheers to the Girls”, featuring Catherine Britt and Fanny Lumsden. 
This song has been the inspiration behind the girls hitting the road together next year for the Love & Lies Tour in the first half of 2017.

Amber has released 22 singles over the course of her career to-date that have either reached #1 or Top 5 on the Country Music Radio Chart and the CMC Video charts.  She’s the winner of the “Telstra Horizon Award” (2010) and above all is well known for her fun and entertaining live shows!!

Amber is also a mentor to young artists in the Australian Country Music industry, each year she is one of the Group Leaders at the Australian Academy of Country Music. In addition, Amber has provided FREE entertainment and mentoring in over 300 schools Australia wide, as part of her ‘Be Your Own Superhero’ program. Amber has a strong connection and affiliation with children, with her first Children’s album “the Kid’s Gone Country” released with a number 1 itunes hit (“My Big Mack Truck”), in May 2016.

Amber has just been announced as the host of iHeart Country Australia’s new radio program ‘Amber Nights’ – where she takes you into the friend zone with Australia’s biggest country stars, plus is a guest presenter on Channel 9’s ‘Getaway’ and is a regular performer for the Sydney Children’s Hospital Telethon on 9.
Selling out shows, and converting people to her style of country music is nothing new for this Sydney city girl and former Qantas accountant. Her ability to engage audiences and tell stories has kept her on the road and working hard for the past 9 years.

She’s played all the major festivals, including The Gympie Muster, Deni Ute Muster and CMC Rocks the Hunter and CMC ROCKS Queensland, has entertained Australia’s Troops in East Timor, UAE and the Sinai, has toured Australia extensively and has one of the most loyal fan bases in the country!

Amber Lawrence - http://www.amberlawrence.com.au
Country Music World - http://countrymusicworld.com.au

The awards keep rolling in for this hardworking Australian, who’s biggest career achievement to date was being awarded the iconic and prestigious ‘Female Artist of the Year’ award, at the 2015 CMAA Golden Guitar awards. 
This was quickly followed up with the Country Music Channel 2015 ‘Female Oz Artist of the Year’ Award.  
This is the first time in history that a female artist has won both awards in one year. In 2016, Amber has released not one, but two albums – the critically acclaimed 5th studio album “Happy Ever After”, and her high selling children’s album “The Kid’s Gone Country”.  And 2017 is shaping up to be another big one for Amber, with two Golden Guitar nominations – for Female Artist of the Year and for Vocal Collaboration of the year for her hit song “Cheers to the Girls”, featuring Catherine Britt and Fanny Lumsden. 
This song has been the inspiration behind the girls hitting the road together next year for the Love & Lies Tour in the first half of 2017.

Amber has released 22 singles over the course of her career to-date that have either reached #1 or Top 5 on the Country Music Radio Chart and the CMC Video charts.  She’s the winner of the “Telstra Horizon Award” (2010) and above all is well known for her fun and entertaining live shows!!

Amber is also a mentor to young artists in the Australian Country Music industry, each year she is one of the Group Leaders at the Australian Academy of Country Music. In addition, Amber has provided FREE entertainment and mentoring in over 300 schools Australia wide, as part of her ‘Be Your Own Superhero’ program. Amber has a strong connection and affiliation with children, with her first Children’s album “the Kid’s Gone Country” released with a number 1 itunes hit (“My Big Mack Truck”), in May 2016.

Amber has just been announced as the host of iHeart Country Australia’s new radio program ‘Amber Nights’ – where she takes you into the friend zone with Australia’s biggest country stars, plus is a guest presenter on Channel 9’s ‘Getaway’ and is a regular performer for the Sydney Children’s Hospital Telethon on 9.
Selling out shows, and converting people to her style of country music is nothing new for this Sydney city girl and former Qantas accountant. Her ability to engage audiences and tell stories has kept her on the road and working hard for the past 9 years.

She’s played all the major festivals, including The Gympie Muster, Deni Ute Muster and CMC Rocks the Hunter and CMC ROCKS Queensland, has entertained Australia’s Troops in East Timor, UAE and the Sinai, has toured Australia extensively and has one of the most loyal fan bases in the country!

snippet.description:
Heartland is a fan’s favorite show that has an immense popularity. It needs a lot of hard work and creativity to create magic on the screen. To make a certain series or a movie, it requires a big production. There should be talented artists, dedicated crew members, super creative writers to collect the fans globally, and many more. snippet.title: See the best & worst Teen Mom engagement rings from Chelsea Houska’s $15K diamond to Amber Portwood’
snippet.description:
THROUGH the years, the Teen Mom franchise has seen several engagements and these are the best and worst rings from Chelsea Houska to Amber Portwood.

Relationships have come and gone on the show, but fans haven't forgotten.
Through the years, fans have watched as stars like Amber Portwood, Chelsea Houska, Jenelle Evans, Kailyn Lowry and more got engaged - in some cases more than once - on the show.

Amber famously got engaged twice on Teen Mom, once to Gary Shirley and once to Matt Baier.

Gary popped the question to his then-girlfriend during the second season of Teen Mom.

He proposed during a beach vacation - the second time he'd done it - and famously stumbled over his words.

Amber yelled at him while he was still down on one knee, but the two did wind up engaged, but never married.

Both the ring and the proposal were memorable.

Teen Mom fans will recall Gary bought the ring at Walmart for a little more than $20.
That's just one of the memorable Teen Mom proposals. Let's take a stroll down memory lane, shall we?
Gary proposed to Amber during Season 2 of Teen Mom.

It wasn't the first time he'd popped the question, but it was certainly a standout.

He proposed with a ring he purchased at Walmart for $21.40 - but it's the thought that counts.

Amber accepted his proposal after berating him for saying the wrong thing, but the engagement didn't last.

Amber has since moved on with several different men, while Gary is married to his wife Christina.

The two have a daughter of their own together, plus one child each from a previous relationship.
Amber got engaged again on Teen Mom several seasons later, this time to then-boyfriend Matt Baier.

Matt proposed to Amber during a romantic dinner date filmed for the show.

The pair split a while later, after Amber learned he was hiding children and other personal matters from her.
Chelsea Houska finally found her dream man, Cole DeBoer, at a gas station in 2014.

The pair dated for a while before getting engaged on the show and tying the knot in 2016.

Cole popped the question in a wooded area he decorated with pictures of the pair and Aubree.

He proposed with a two-carat engagement ring is estimated to have cost somewhere between $12,000 and $15,000.
Catelynn Lowell and Tyler Baltierra are high school sweethearts.

The pair appeared on 16 and Pregnant, documenting their adoption journey, and then appearing on Teen Mom.

They got engaged during a fancy night out and Tyler upgraded Catelynn's ring several times - once on Christmas 2014 and another time with a limited-edition Beauty and the Beast ring on Catelynn's birthday.

The ring cost more than $1,000 and may have come from Zales, according to Mommy Things.

snippet.title: Heartland star Amber Marshall (Amy Fleming) facts you may not know | Husband, Net Worth, Pregnant
snippet.description:
Hey everyone. Welcome to Soap Trend. We hope that everybody is doing well. We have some exciting news to share with you all in today’s video. In this video, we present you with some of the interesting facts about our favorite TV actress Amber Marshall who is popularly known as Amy Fleming from Heartland. Let’s get started.

Amber Marshall who was born on June 2, 1988 is a Canadian actress, singer, and equestrian. She has appeared in several television films and series, most notably as Amy Fleming in the long-running CBC series Heartland. For her performance in the series, Marshall won the inaugural Canada's Screen Star Award at the 1st Canadian Screen Awards. Marshall was born and raised in London, Ontario. A former veterinary assistant, Marshall has been riding horses since she could barely walk and says that the two things she loves the most are "acting and horses". Amber attended Lester B. Pearson School for the Arts, starting to act at the early age of 11 and growing up she went to the Original Kids Theater Company. Here are a series of interesting facts about Amber Marshall. #Heartland #AmberMarshall #AmyFleming

snippet.title: Top 10 Hits: Amber
snippet.description:
Marie-Claire "Amber" Cremers (born 17 September 1969) is a Dutch-born German singer, songwriter, label owner, and executive producer. 
Between 1996 to 2006 she scored in the U.S. charts 5 Top-100 hits and 12 Top-10 hits in Billboard's Dance/Club chart which 5 of them peaked at No'1.
Her debut hit 'This is Your Night' peaked at No'1 in Israel,No'3 in Spain No'11 in Australia, No'14 in The Netherlands and No'24 on U.S. Top-100.
In December 2016, Billboard ranked her as the 34th most successful dance artist of all-time.
